laboratory_examinations.findings: The patient's tumor was a moderately cellular neoplasm formed by bland neoplastic neurons, oligodendroglial-like cells, and adipocytes. Neural rosettes were numerous. No evidence of necrosis or tumor-related vascular changes. Immunopositivity for NeuN, microtubule-associated protein 2 (MAP-2), and synaptophysin. Focal GFAP labeling. Immunonegative for IDH1-R132H. Rare p53 immunopositivity and less than 1% Ki 67 immunopositivity.
Showed no deletions of 1p, 19q, or TP53 and no amplification of the epidermal growth factor receptor gene.

Moderately to densely cellular neoplasm that was well circumscribed with focal areas of vascular hyalinosis. Predominantly spindle-shaped tumor cells with long eosinophilic processes. Similar immunoprofile to the daughter's tumor without staining for p53.
